1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:04,546
<i>Erica, I still want to save my brother.</i>
<i>I don't want him to die.</i>

2
00:00:04,629 --> 00:00:07,090
<i>But if anything happened to you,</i>
<i>I won't be able to bear it.</i>

3
00:00:09,467 --> 00:00:12,679
<i>If there's something going on between</i>
<i>you and Lucas, you have to tell Mel.</i>

4
00:00:12,762 --> 00:00:13,638
<i>There's nothing between us--</i>

5
00:00:13,722 --> 00:00:15,348
<i>Mel saw you two last night.</i>

6
00:00:15,432 --> 00:00:18,309
<i>But the way you two are</i>
<i>when you're together, it's not nothing.</i>

7
00:00:18,393 --> 00:00:19,769
<i>Every time I see you together.</i>

8
00:00:19,853 --> 00:00:21,062
<i>Things are different now.</i>

9
00:00:21,146 --> 00:00:23,064
<i>We're looking for two</i>
<i>killers right now, Marco.</i>

10
00:00:23,148 --> 00:00:26,025
<i>Do you really think I have time</i>
<i>to think about my romantic feelings?</i>

11
00:00:26,109 --> 00:00:28,111
<i>Edward, something</i>
<i>happened there yesterday.</i>

12
00:00:28,194 --> 00:00:30,655
<i>Sorry, my mother was just panicking.</i>

13
00:00:30,739 --> 00:00:33,324
<i>I thought I saw Edong here in the house.</i>

14
00:00:33,408 --> 00:00:35,160
<i>But it was just my imagination.</i>

15
00:00:35,243 --> 00:00:36,745
<i>You cunning demon.</i>

16
00:00:36,828 --> 00:00:38,496
<i>You've been there all along.</i>

17
00:00:38,580 --> 00:00:40,749
<i>Deceiving everyone</i>
<i>into thinking you're normal.</i>

18
00:00:40,832 --> 00:00:44,127
<i>You won't stop me from getting to Alice,</i>

19
00:00:44,210 --> 00:00:47,964
<i>or Mel, or Beth, or Erica.</i>

20
00:00:48,047 --> 00:00:50,759
<i>I'll stand on top of your dead body</i>

21
00:00:50,842 --> 00:00:52,802
<i>if that's what it takes to get them all.</i>

22
00:00:52,886 --> 00:00:54,846
[sinister laughs]

23
00:00:56,848 --> 00:01:02,062
[unsettling music playing]

24
00:01:17,827 --> 00:01:23,708
[unsettling music continues]

25
00:01:29,339 --> 00:01:36,304
[theme music playing]

26
00:02:45,331 --> 00:02:47,834
Please let me come back again, Pa.

27
00:02:47,917 --> 00:02:49,669
You should be asking your mom.

28
00:02:49,752 --> 00:02:51,212
Good day, sirs.

29
00:02:51,296 --> 00:02:55,216
- [engine sputtering]
- [foreboding music playing]

30
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:57,719
[grunts] Please drive, boss.

31
00:02:57,802 --> 00:02:59,220
Just go straight ahead.

32
00:03:08,062 --> 00:03:13,484
[foreboding music continues, fades]

33
00:03:13,568 --> 00:03:14,527
[woman] Grandpa.

34
00:03:15,403 --> 00:03:17,447
- [rooster crows]
- Have some water.

35
00:03:18,573 --> 00:03:21,284
- Oh. Uh…
- Find cover. It's drizzling.

36
00:03:21,367 --> 00:03:23,161
[Edong panting]

37
00:03:23,244 --> 00:03:24,787
Thank you so much, dear.

38
00:03:25,788 --> 00:03:27,165
I'm fine.

39
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:30,209
[slurps]

40
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:32,712
[chuckles] It's good.

41
00:03:33,171 --> 00:03:34,714
You remind me of my grandfather.

42
00:03:34,797 --> 00:03:36,758
[Edong chuckling]

43
00:03:36,841 --> 00:03:40,553
I suppose he's handsome too. [chuckles]

44
00:03:40,637 --> 00:03:42,430
Yes, he's a joker like you.

45
00:03:42,513 --> 00:03:44,224
[both chuckle]

46
00:03:44,849 --> 00:03:46,059
Thank you, dear.

47
00:03:46,142 --> 00:03:48,061
Alright, Grandpa. I'll go back inside.

48
00:03:51,147 --> 00:03:53,650
- [rooster crows]
- [chuckles] What?

49
00:03:55,151 --> 00:03:56,319
Why did you hire him?

50
00:03:56,402 --> 00:03:59,322
Look at him. He's so old,
he can't even stand properly.

51
00:03:59,405 --> 00:04:02,075
[woman] Hey, he might hear you.

52
00:04:02,951 --> 00:04:04,661
I just felt sorry for him.

53
00:04:08,373 --> 00:04:10,291
<i>You're the new owner of this house?</i>

54
00:04:11,084 --> 00:04:14,003
<i>Ma'am, I used to be a gardener here,</i>

55
00:04:14,087 --> 00:04:17,799
<i>but I had to leave</i>
<i>because my grandchild got sick.</i>

56
00:04:19,008 --> 00:04:20,134
<i>Too bad.</i>

57
00:04:20,218 --> 00:04:23,179
<i>I thought I could offer</i>
<i>labor in exchange for quick cash</i>

58
00:04:23,263 --> 00:04:25,473
<i>to buy meds for my grandchild.</i>

59
00:04:27,058 --> 00:04:30,561
<i>Ma'am, do you perhaps need a gardener?</i>

60
00:04:31,145 --> 00:04:32,605
<i>Even just temporary?</i>

61
00:04:33,147 --> 00:04:35,149
<i>I just need to buy my</i>
<i>grandchild's medication.</i>

62
00:04:35,233 --> 00:04:39,195
[foreboding music playing]

63
00:04:39,279 --> 00:04:40,905
[woman] He's not asking for alms.

64
00:04:40,989 --> 00:04:42,657
He offered to do the job.

65
00:04:42,740 --> 00:04:46,411
He's not asking for much.
Can't we give it to him?

66
00:04:46,494 --> 00:04:49,330
Come on. We've got more to unpack.

67
00:04:49,414 --> 00:04:50,665
You're being too paranoid.

68
00:04:50,748 --> 00:04:56,462
[foreboding music continues]

69
00:05:00,883 --> 00:05:02,176
[ominous music sting]

70
00:05:02,260 --> 00:05:03,970
- [Alice] So, it's not Kyle.
- [music fades]

71
00:05:04,762 --> 00:05:07,932
He said he was with
Michelle the night Louisa was murdered.

72
00:05:08,016 --> 00:05:10,310
Michele already corroborated his alibi.

73
00:05:11,185 --> 00:05:13,938
So, where do we go from here?

74
00:05:14,814 --> 00:05:16,065
Why is it always like this?

75
00:05:16,566 --> 00:05:19,819
Every lead or theory
we follow brings us to a dead end.

76
00:05:19,902 --> 00:05:22,405
Don't tell me you're
back to accusing Edong.

77
00:05:22,488 --> 00:05:24,365
Well, you can't blame me.

78
00:05:24,866 --> 00:05:29,037
We just keep going in circles,
and it always leads us back to Edong.

79
00:05:31,622 --> 00:05:35,043
But you said you're sure
about the scar on the killer's back--

80
00:05:35,126 --> 00:05:36,169
I am sure!

81
00:05:36,753 --> 00:05:38,004
I didn't say you weren't!

82
00:05:38,755 --> 00:05:41,549
But here we are again, without a suspect.

83
00:05:41,632 --> 00:05:43,384
We've already blamed everyone.

84
00:05:43,468 --> 00:05:45,845
[Marco sighs deeply]

85
00:05:45,928 --> 00:05:48,639
I'll help the police find Edong.

86
00:05:49,474 --> 00:05:50,725
He is here in Amurao.

87
00:05:51,225 --> 00:05:53,644
If we don't stop,
we'll find him eventually.

88
00:05:56,564 --> 00:05:57,982
Ryan and I will help too.

89
00:06:00,151 --> 00:06:06,699
[tense music playing]

90
00:06:13,039 --> 00:06:17,627
[indistinct laughter, chatter on TV]

91
00:06:17,710 --> 00:06:20,046
<i>- What happened?</i>
<i>- Whoo!</i>

92
00:06:20,129 --> 00:06:23,841
[man 1] <i>Your son's</i>
<i>better at dreaming than farming!</i>

93
00:06:23,925 --> 00:06:25,343
[man 2] <i>Are you hurt?</i>

94
00:06:25,426 --> 00:06:26,469
[boy] <i>No, Pa.</i>

95
00:06:26,552 --> 00:06:28,638
<i>- You know what, Pa?</i>
<i>- What?</i>

96
00:06:29,222 --> 00:06:32,225
<i>- Mama told me something.</i>
<i>- What did she say?</i>

97
00:06:32,308 --> 00:06:37,605
[unsettling music playing]

98
00:07:03,965 --> 00:07:09,178
[unsettling music continues]

99
00:07:26,112 --> 00:07:31,909
[music turns sinister]

100
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:49,385
[sinister music continues]

101
00:08:04,942 --> 00:08:10,031
[sinister music continues]

102
00:08:33,137 --> 00:08:38,893
[sinister music intensifies]

103
00:08:48,611 --> 00:08:50,821
[Kitkat crying on video]

104
00:08:50,905 --> 00:08:53,783
[crying]<i> Mama!</i>

105
00:08:54,450 --> 00:08:58,246
<i>Give me back to Mama!</i>

106
00:08:58,329 --> 00:09:00,331
[music fades]

107
00:09:03,292 --> 00:09:05,461
- [suspenseful music playing]
- [door opens]

108
00:09:05,545 --> 00:09:07,505
[man 3 on TV] <i>What brings you here, Paeng?</i>

109
00:09:07,588 --> 00:09:10,049
<i>How can I help you?</i>

110
00:09:10,132 --> 00:09:13,636
[boy] <i>The horses</i>
<i>look like they'll come alive!</i>

111
00:09:13,719 --> 00:09:16,013
<i>They look so real!</i>

112
00:09:16,097 --> 00:09:18,266
<i>And there's the Caterpillar!</i>

113
00:09:18,349 --> 00:09:22,186
<i>Ma'am Rhea said that's what it's called.</i>

114
00:09:22,270 --> 00:09:24,689
<i>Its engine is so loud!</i>

115
00:09:24,772 --> 00:09:26,857
<i>Chug-chug-chug!</i>

116
00:09:26,941 --> 00:09:29,277
<i>It sounds like an approaching train!</i>

117
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:32,321
[girl] <i>Are there many toys there?</i>

118
00:09:32,405 --> 00:09:36,409
- [boy] <i>Oh, you said it!</i>
- [suspenseful music crescendos]

119
00:09:39,954 --> 00:09:42,623
Hmm, so was it all a lie?

120
00:09:42,707 --> 00:09:45,334
The kindness, warm smiles,

121
00:09:45,418 --> 00:09:49,046
that you showed to everyone…
your seemingly perfect life

122
00:09:49,964 --> 00:09:52,008
Was that all just hiding a monster?

123
00:09:52,091 --> 00:09:55,595
I mean, that's
everyone's question right now, right?

124
00:09:55,678 --> 00:09:56,470
[chuckles]

125
00:09:56,554 --> 00:09:58,931
Bro, I think people just misunderstood.

126
00:09:59,015 --> 00:10:01,892
You were, you know, this model husband.

127
00:10:02,268 --> 00:10:04,478
An inspiration to a lot of guys out there.

128
00:10:04,562 --> 00:10:07,982
But all of a sudden, there are so
many accusations coming out against you.

129
00:10:08,441 --> 00:10:09,442
[sighs heavily]

130
00:10:11,110 --> 00:10:12,570
I understand.

131
00:10:13,696 --> 00:10:16,032
And I'm glad you asked because…

132
00:10:16,115 --> 00:10:17,366
[uneasy music playing]

133
00:10:17,450 --> 00:10:21,078
…there are so many
questions that are needed to be asked.

134
00:10:21,996 --> 00:10:23,456
Like, why stay that long?

135
00:10:24,540 --> 00:10:27,126
If you've been abused
from the very beginning,

136
00:10:27,543 --> 00:10:29,420
why didn't you leave right away?

137
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:31,213
You're Mel Barrera.

138
00:10:31,297 --> 00:10:34,592
You have a great career, a good family,

139
00:10:34,675 --> 00:10:36,594
and you're financially stable.

140
00:10:37,345 --> 00:10:39,138
You are an empowered woman.

141
00:10:39,555 --> 00:10:42,808
So, why suffer when
you could have just walked away?

142
00:10:42,892 --> 00:10:46,896
- [uneasy music continues, fades]
- [breathes deeply]

143
00:10:47,813 --> 00:10:49,357
Okay, so, uh…

144
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:52,652
When people think about abused wives,

145
00:10:53,569 --> 00:10:57,531
they automatically think
that this is someone who's helpless,

146
00:10:58,282 --> 00:11:00,785
someone who needs a man just to survive.

147
00:11:01,202 --> 00:11:04,747
But what people
actually need to understand,

148
00:11:04,830 --> 00:11:07,541
especially women,

149
00:11:07,958 --> 00:11:11,462
is that it can happen to anyone.

150
00:11:12,755 --> 00:11:16,175
I mean, you can
have everything in the world.

151
00:11:16,550 --> 00:11:18,511
And a man can come in

152
00:11:18,594 --> 00:11:20,971
and still make you feel
like none of that matters.

153
00:11:21,055 --> 00:11:22,390
[melancholic music playing]

154
00:11:22,473 --> 00:11:25,976
He can use your insecurities against you

155
00:11:26,769 --> 00:11:28,562
and make you doubt your own worth.

156
00:11:28,646 --> 00:11:31,065
[melancholic music continues]

157
00:11:31,148 --> 00:11:33,359
He can gaslight you.

158
00:11:33,442 --> 00:11:35,486
He can mess with your head

159
00:11:35,569 --> 00:11:38,614
and make you think
that you're nothing without him.

160
00:11:40,116 --> 00:11:41,325
And he can make you think

161
00:11:41,409 --> 00:11:44,161
that the career and
reputation you've built for yourself

162
00:11:44,245 --> 00:11:47,540
all those years,
everything that you've worked hard for…

163
00:11:48,791 --> 00:11:51,127
can disappear in an instant.

164
00:11:52,294 --> 00:11:53,796
And you lose everything.

165
00:11:55,423 --> 00:11:58,050
When you hear that over and over again,

166
00:11:58,551 --> 00:11:59,844
the tendency is…

167
00:11:59,927 --> 00:12:01,804
[music becomes unsettling]

168
00:12:01,887 --> 00:12:03,681
…you start to believe it.

169
00:12:04,223 --> 00:12:07,435
[Gio] <i>But why does</i>
<i>she have to lie about this, bro?</i>

170
00:12:07,518 --> 00:12:11,230
It was such a big lie, bro, you know.

171
00:12:11,313 --> 00:12:12,815
Why would she do that?

172
00:12:13,274 --> 00:12:15,484
[inhales deeply] Actually… [exhales]

173
00:12:15,568 --> 00:12:17,027
[unsettling music continues]

174
00:12:17,111 --> 00:12:19,029
I've been asking myself the same question.

175
00:12:20,030 --> 00:12:21,157
If she wanted out,

176
00:12:22,324 --> 00:12:24,076
she could have just left, right?

177
00:12:25,453 --> 00:12:27,955
Why does she have to destroy me

178
00:12:28,372 --> 00:12:29,665
and herself?

179
00:12:30,166 --> 00:12:33,419
Does she really think all this drama
is going to help her in the end?

180
00:12:33,502 --> 00:12:37,465
Or maybe she thinks she's too big…

181
00:12:39,175 --> 00:12:40,551
too untouchable.

182
00:12:41,385 --> 00:12:43,512
And she just wants to show me

183
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:45,848
- how easy it is for her to destroy me.
- [music fades]

184
00:12:45,931 --> 00:12:48,851
Well, that can be said about you, too.

185
00:12:48,934 --> 00:12:52,813
[tense music playing]

186
00:12:52,897 --> 00:12:54,190
You're famous, Anton.

187
00:12:54,273 --> 00:12:56,275
You have a devoted following.

188
00:12:56,358 --> 00:12:59,737
And your family is
like a big political family.

189
00:12:59,820 --> 00:13:03,991
It can be argued
that you can do anything to a woman

190
00:13:04,492 --> 00:13:08,746
and be confident
enough to escape accountability.

191
00:13:08,829 --> 00:13:13,250
- [breathes deeply]
- [tense music continues]

192
00:13:16,295 --> 00:13:19,423
I can assure
you that isn't what is happening here.

193
00:13:20,049 --> 00:13:22,092
I have been suspended from work.

194
00:13:22,176 --> 00:13:24,303
I've been getting all this hate.

195
00:13:25,471 --> 00:13:26,847
And now,

196
00:13:26,931 --> 00:13:28,390
I have to fight in court

197
00:13:29,350 --> 00:13:31,310
to clear my name.

198
00:13:31,393 --> 00:13:33,354
I'm being held accountable for something

199
00:13:33,437 --> 00:13:34,897
that I didn't even do.

200
00:13:34,980 --> 00:13:36,982
Anyone who is innocent…

201
00:13:37,066 --> 00:13:38,984
If you accuse them of
something they didn't do,

202
00:13:40,569 --> 00:13:42,613
if you do them an injustice,

203
00:13:44,990 --> 00:13:48,202
they would really go crazy.

204
00:13:48,285 --> 00:13:53,791
[tense music continues]

205
00:13:58,712 --> 00:14:00,172
What the fuck was that?

206
00:14:00,923 --> 00:14:02,424
That bitch was trying to trap me!

207
00:14:02,508 --> 00:14:05,344
I thought you made me go
there because they were on my side!

208
00:14:06,428 --> 00:14:08,013
That fucking bitch!

209
00:14:08,097 --> 00:14:09,515
All women are the same!

210
00:14:09,598 --> 00:14:12,601
[tense music continues, fades]

211
00:14:12,685 --> 00:14:14,270
That interview was a winner.

212
00:14:14,353 --> 00:14:16,647
I really felt your honesty.

213
00:14:16,730 --> 00:14:19,692
You were able to say
everything you wanted to say.

214
00:14:20,276 --> 00:14:21,485
[clicks mouth]

215
00:14:21,569 --> 00:14:23,988
I'm so proud of you, dear.

216
00:14:24,071 --> 00:14:25,030
You are?

217
00:14:25,114 --> 00:14:28,033
Of course! I've always been proud of you.

218
00:14:28,117 --> 00:14:29,952
I should have said it earlier.

219
00:14:30,578 --> 00:14:34,874
I promise I will keep
saying it from now on.

220
00:14:37,042 --> 00:14:42,256
[poignant music playing]

221
00:14:42,339 --> 00:14:43,632
What is it?

222
00:14:49,221 --> 00:14:50,514
I still love him, Mom.

223
00:14:54,852 --> 00:14:56,270
Lucas.

224
00:14:57,438 --> 00:14:58,939
We had an affair, but…

225
00:15:00,399 --> 00:15:03,611
It was a long time ago,
but I think I still love him.

226
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:07,823
I don't know what to do.

227
00:15:07,907 --> 00:15:14,121
[poignant music continues, fades]

228
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:18,500
[ominous music playing]

229
00:15:18,584 --> 00:15:19,668
So…

230
00:15:20,336 --> 00:15:21,420
did you do it?

231
00:15:21,503 --> 00:15:22,713
[man] <i>Of course, sir.</i>

232
00:15:22,796 --> 00:15:23,964
<i>As I've told you…</i>

233
00:15:24,048 --> 00:15:25,758
for such a big amount of money,

234
00:15:25,841 --> 00:15:29,178
I can do anything and everything.

235
00:15:29,261 --> 00:15:33,807
[ominous music continues]

236
00:15:38,020 --> 00:15:39,146
[cop 1] Everything looks okay.

237
00:15:39,229 --> 00:15:40,648
[cop 2] Let's wait for them.

238
00:15:40,731 --> 00:15:42,066
[car approaches, tires screech]

239
00:15:42,149 --> 00:15:43,317
[cop 1] Hey.

240
00:15:48,489 --> 00:15:49,615
[cop 3] We've arrived.

241
00:15:49,698 --> 00:15:51,158
[cop 1] Alright,
you can take it from here.

242
00:15:51,241 --> 00:15:53,410
- Come on.
- [cop 2] Okay, sir.

243
00:15:54,536 --> 00:15:56,246
[car doors close]

244
00:15:56,330 --> 00:15:59,708
[engine revs]

245
00:16:00,793 --> 00:16:04,254
[man] We already
told you to leave, didn't we?

246
00:16:04,838 --> 00:16:06,382
Even if you work longer hours,

247
00:16:06,924 --> 00:16:08,425
we'll still pay the same amount.

248
00:16:08,509 --> 00:16:09,969
I'll pay you myself.

249
00:16:10,052 --> 00:16:11,929
You might rip off my wife otherwise.

250
00:16:13,347 --> 00:16:18,602
Arrogance leads to downfall.

251
00:16:19,561 --> 00:16:23,649
Those who act high
and mighty will be humbled.

252
00:16:23,732 --> 00:16:24,692
What did you say?

253
00:16:24,775 --> 00:16:29,029
Tell your wife I said thanks.

254
00:16:31,532 --> 00:16:33,283
Don't come back here!

255
00:16:33,367 --> 00:16:38,414
[ominous music continues]

256
00:16:48,882 --> 00:16:51,301
[Susan] <i>Wait here, Alice.</i>

257
00:16:51,385 --> 00:16:56,056
[eerie music playing]

258
00:17:01,812 --> 00:17:03,564
[dramatic music sting]

259
00:17:03,647 --> 00:17:08,694
[eerie music continues]

260
00:17:16,452 --> 00:17:21,999
[eerie music continues]

261
00:17:28,005 --> 00:17:29,923
[music fades]

262
00:17:30,007 --> 00:17:31,133
I can't.

263
00:17:31,508 --> 00:17:32,676
I can't.

264
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:36,013
It’s like my brain doesn't
want to remember what happened.

265
00:17:36,096 --> 00:17:40,517
Again, it's protecting you from something
you are not ready to face yet.

266
00:17:40,601 --> 00:17:41,935
But I am.

267
00:17:42,478 --> 00:17:43,437
I am ready.

268
00:17:44,271 --> 00:17:46,523
I've been traumatized
and devastated enough.

269
00:17:46,607 --> 00:17:49,485
What else could I find out
that could devastate me even more?

270
00:17:49,568 --> 00:17:51,653
- [tense music swells]
<i>- Ma!</i>

271
00:17:52,279 --> 00:17:53,280
[glass breaks]

272
00:17:53,363 --> 00:17:54,907
[Susan]<i> You went</i>
<i>missing when you were five.</i>

273
00:17:54,990 --> 00:17:58,285
<i>We found you at night,</i>
<i>crying alone at a vacant lot.</i>

274
00:17:58,368 --> 00:18:00,537
<i>Your dad and I think that's</i>
<i>where your fear of the dark started.</i>

275
00:18:00,621 --> 00:18:02,581
[Scott] <i>Taking my</i>
<i>son without a return date.</i>

276
00:18:02,664 --> 00:18:04,083
<i>Alice, that's called kidnapping!</i>

277
00:18:04,166 --> 00:18:06,710
[Alice]<i> I don’t remember</i>
<i>exactly what you did, but my body does.</i>

278
00:18:06,794 --> 00:18:07,920
[Scott] <i>Alice, stop.</i>

279
00:18:08,003 --> 00:18:10,005
- [Alice] <i>Why do I keep remembering it?</i>
- [Beth]<i> Alice, calm down.</i>

280
00:18:10,089 --> 00:18:12,966
<i>This is crazy! I'm going crazy!</i>

281
00:18:13,050 --> 00:18:16,011
<i>I blame this all on him.</i>
<i>Whoever took me when I was five.</i>

282
00:18:16,095 --> 00:18:18,972
<i>The trauma, nightmares…</i>
<i>All of this came out of that.</i>

283
00:18:19,056 --> 00:18:21,809
<i>I am like this because of that.</i>

284
00:18:21,892 --> 00:18:24,728
<i>Ten hours.</i>
<i>A lot can happen within that time, right?</i>

285
00:18:24,812 --> 00:18:27,064
[tense music continues]

286
00:18:27,147 --> 00:18:28,857
- I'm ready, I'm ready.
- [music fades]

287
00:18:29,525 --> 00:18:32,194
Why doesn't my brain want to show me?

288
00:18:33,403 --> 00:18:34,321
[Edward grunts]

289
00:18:37,282 --> 00:18:39,910
Hey, be careful.

290
00:18:40,494 --> 00:18:41,954
[sighs] Careful.

291
00:18:43,288 --> 00:18:44,248
[grunts]

292
00:18:46,625 --> 00:18:47,626
Go on, Heart.

293
00:18:48,794 --> 00:18:50,045
Almost there.

294
00:18:51,046 --> 00:18:52,214
Just a bit more.

295
00:18:52,881 --> 00:18:54,091
[chuckles]

296
00:18:56,301 --> 00:18:57,636
Okay.

297
00:19:26,999 --> 00:19:28,458
[exhales deeply] Heart.

298
00:19:34,214 --> 00:19:35,591
I wish you'd seen her, Heart.

299
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:41,513
She was so small.

300
00:19:43,932 --> 00:19:45,475
So innocent.

301
00:19:46,435 --> 00:19:48,520
[chuckles]

302
00:19:49,271 --> 00:19:52,482
I even brought home something she owned.

303
00:19:54,318 --> 00:19:55,569
I want to…

304
00:19:56,612 --> 00:20:00,032
[unsettling music playing]

305
00:20:00,115 --> 00:20:02,201
I want to keep her in my memory forever.

306
00:20:25,015 --> 00:20:26,642
But…

307
00:20:26,725 --> 00:20:33,148
[unsettling music continues]

308
00:20:50,832 --> 00:20:52,918
she still doesn't compare to her.

309
00:20:56,088 --> 00:20:57,839
None of them do.

310
00:20:57,923 --> 00:21:03,762
[unsettling music continues]

311
00:21:15,315 --> 00:21:17,317
She's still my favorite.

312
00:21:19,736 --> 00:21:24,199
[unsettling music intensifies]

313
00:21:37,629 --> 00:21:42,134
[music becomes sinister]

314
00:21:43,010 --> 00:21:45,554
- [student] <i>This is gold, dude!</i>
<i>- Really? Inside the school?</i>

315
00:21:45,637 --> 00:21:48,640
<i>It's my face, but it's not me!</i>

316
00:21:49,099 --> 00:21:51,184
<i>It's not me!</i>

317
00:21:51,268 --> 00:21:52,853
<i>They violated Mel,</i>
<i>and you expect me to do nothing?!</i>

318
00:21:52,936 --> 00:21:54,021
<i>I know you love Mel,</i>

319
00:21:54,104 --> 00:21:57,190
<i>but what she needs now is</i>
<i>to win her case against Anton.</i>

320
00:21:57,274 --> 00:21:59,026
<i>This isn't about how I feel about Mel.</i>

321
00:21:59,109 --> 00:22:01,028
<i>It's in the past.</i>
<i>I don't have feelings for her anymore.</i>

322
00:22:01,111 --> 00:22:04,948
<i>After this scandal, he's</i>
<i>the only one who'll love and accept me,</i>

323
00:22:05,032 --> 00:22:07,701
<i>and you want to take him from me, Erica?!</i>

324
00:22:07,784 --> 00:22:10,537
<i>You want to break free from a man,</i>
<i>just to focus on another one?!</i>

325
00:22:10,620 --> 00:22:12,956
<i>- Come on, Mel! Are you serious?!</i>
<i>- Yes, Attorney!</i>

326
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:14,875
[Alice]
<i>She's falling apart in front of us.</i>

327
00:22:14,958 --> 00:22:16,543
<i>I can't even do anything to help her.</i>

328
00:22:16,626 --> 00:22:17,919
<i>Are you really okay with us leaving?</i>

329
00:22:18,003 --> 00:22:20,172
<i>We have no choice.</i>
<i>We have to protect Seth.</i>

330
00:22:20,255 --> 00:22:22,632
<i>I'll get you, Alice.</i>

331
00:22:22,716 --> 00:22:24,051
<i>You and your monster.</i>

332
00:22:24,134 --> 00:22:27,054
<i>None of you can escape.</i>
